  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The context of use narrative explicitly states that the pump impeller tip speed must remain below 4 m/s under all evaluated operating conditions to prevent catastrophic red blood cell lysis; this tip-speed constraint is a safety-critical property of the intended use. However, the bound requirement set addresses only relative hemolysis index acceptance and flow-rate envelope compliance, and does not enumerate the tip-speed constraint as a formal obligation.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou1-cpb-req-set-v1",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou1-cpb-hemolysis-claim",
